HEADWORD: Conscionable
<hw>Con"scion*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Irregularly
formed fr. <ets>conscience</ets>.]</ety> <def>Governed by, or according
to, conscience; reasonable; just.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let my debtors have <qex>conscionable</qex> satisfaction.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir H. Wotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conscionableness</ent>⟦br⟧
